{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/hydrangeas-in-a-sacred-mountain/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"7f9ec6c3-45a9-526a-9f39-c6b47d1629e3","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/1f853/hydrangeas.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/01472/hydrangeas.webp 240w,\n/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/222bd/hydrangeas.webp 480w,\n/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/620b9/hydrangeas.webp 960w,\n/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/86447/hydrangeas.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/3bc27/hydrangeas.jpg 240w,\n/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/98431/hydrangeas.jpg 480w,\n/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/b3ee8/hydrangeas.jpg 960w,\n/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/1f853/hydrangeas.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/ab6d2f7588825df8d0e33c9f00cdab11/b3ee8/hydrangeas.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Hydrangeas in a Sacred Mountain\"\n          title=\"Hydrangeas in a Sacred Mountain\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I saw a lot of beautiful hydrangeas in the sacred place Mt.Yoshino.<br>\nEvery clusters were so big and filled with energy. I felt this was reality. My eyes opened. I’d like to keep it in my mind.</p>\n<p>In this year, I’m interested in reading postmodern books more.<br>\nEspecially literature, philosophy and criticism spark my curiosity. Active authors provide me with inspiration and guidance. I receive divine afflatus through them.</p>\n<p>For instance…  </p>\n<p>鏡の中を数える (Counting the Inside of a Mirror) by Prabda Yoon<br>\n<a href=\"http://www.typhoonbooksjapan.com/e/catalogue/kagami_no_naka.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.typhoonbooksjapan.com/e/catalogue/kagami<em>no</em>naka.html</a>  </p>\n<p>ゲンロン (Genron) by Hiroki Azuma(ed.), et al<br>\n<a href=\"https://genron-tomonokai.com/genron/en/\" target=\"_blank\">https://genron-tomonokai.com/genron/en/</a>  </p>\n<p>These books teach me a possible next step in the future. The step is not too emotional. And it’s not too logical. It’s cool as a cucumber and so kind.</p>\n<p>I like things I can feel a ray of sunshine.<br>\nAll experiences are very good openers to open my eyes.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/hydrangeas-in-a-sacred-mountain/","tagSlugs":["/tag/book/","/tag/literature/","/tag/philosophy/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-07-22T06:40:32.169Z","description":"I saw a lot of beautiful hydrangeas in the sacred place Mt.Yoshino. Every clusters were so big and...","tags":["Book","Literature","Philosophy"],"title":"Hydrangeas in a Sacred Mountain","socialImage":"/media/hydrangeas.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/hydrangeas-in-a-sacred-mountain/"}}}